This works around the issue:
```patch
diff --git a/src/Framework/TestCase.php b/src/Framework/TestCase.php
index 600008c32..61a8fe45d 100644
--- a/src/Framework/TestCase.php
+++ b/src/Framework/TestCase.php
@@ -26,7 +26,6 @@
 use function array_search;
 use function array_unique;
 use function array_values;
-use function assert;
 use function basename;
 use function call_user_func;
 use function chdir;
@@ -1996,7 +1995,7 @@ private function verifyMockObjects(): void
                 foreach ($this->prophet->getProphecies() as $objectProphecy) {
                     foreach ($objectProphecy->getMethodProphecies() as $methodProphecies) {
                         foreach ($methodProphecies as $methodProphecy) {
-                            assert($methodProphecy instanceof MethodProphecy);
+                            \assert($methodProphecy instanceof MethodProphecy);
```

@nikic Assuming case insensitivity, the (following) code has a naming collision:

```php
use function \assert;

class foo extends Assert { }
```
